Officer of Peacekeepers, Karana<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/12/01 1:23:15 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear.</span><hr size=1> KCoG is NOT the overseer of all events on Karana (dragons, planes etc.) that is KGC (Karana Guild Central). <br>
<br>
Secondly, it is a standing policy on raids that OOC complaints and/or harrassment is not tolerated. Period. Had it occured and been brought to Kellory's attention, OR had Kellory himself seen it, I'm sure the perpetrators would have been warned/kicked off. <br>
<br>
Thirdly, lots of tells go back and forth on a raid. A simple &quot;Yes, I'm ready&quot; to the rezzing cleric would have been fine. More words just confused the situation it appears. <br>
